This whole block of code is hard to follow if you're coming in without in-depth knowledge of Docker image tag names, like me. Suggestions to make it easier to read and modify if any issues come up:

Have example Docker tags in code comments, e.g.,

// image is something like "postgres:latest"
splitDocker = image.split("/");
splitTag = splitDocker[1].split(":");


Break the method up into smaller functions. May be hard, because this is an interface, and also because you've got http calls peppered throughout.
Write unit tests (not integration tests) so you can test the different formats.

These suggestions are not mutually exclusive. :)
You don't want to over-engineer this, so use your discretion on this one.

